<br>
1)  Run around and click 30-40 things that drop stuff you want (spiders, cats etc)<br>
2) stop near zone wall (or other stationary object) so i don't pushed<br>
3)  Channel Jyll's<br>
4)  almost everything will be dead, may need to repeat once loot and repeat.  <br>
<br>
This works best with sow or soe as you can run and consequently pull faster.  <br>
<br>
If you do this a couple of times, you usually net ~200 pp in tradeskill stuff (silk, pelts, etc).  <br>
<br>
Normally takes about 5 minutes to round one up and loot.  <br>
<br>
You have to sell it in the bazaar, but if you just leave your guy in trader mode while you sleep or go to dinner, the stuff disappears pretty fast.<br>
<br>
tip:  sit thirty seconds after you finish the carnage to allow all of the empty corpses to dissappear.<br>
<br>
tip:  Don't be greedy with the price, after you see how easy it is to farm these items for wizards and bards you will realize it doesn't make good sense to spend 10pp per spider silk.  Someone will undercut you and you will never sell, stick to 1-2 pp per silk and 5pp per high/medium quality pelt.  It is still worth it.  As always check the bazaar to see what other people are selling for.<br>
<br>
Zones:  EK, SRO (ac farming at the same time), Stonebrunt?  <br>
<br>
Question:  are there any other zones that people know about that this type of strategy would work?  I also have access to an enchanter so if the mobs were higher level i would be able to chain stun them too if needed.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elharinalokhem>Elharina Lokhem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 336<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/3/03 12:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another unoriginal question about where to farm plat</span><hr size=1> Use to find that PoN mephits were awesome loot (but needs a group) seem to remember turning over 30k in a day there from tradeskill stuff alone (couple of spectrals and tons of ethereals too) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=113259" target="top">Sage Elharina Lokhem 65th Season Wizard</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
